		<![CDATA[<b>Police Look For Internet Predator</b>

Carla White was a popular 13-year-old and a good student. But she was also meeting strangers on the Internet. Last May, Carla was found strangled to death, and police believe she met her killer online. “I can’t believe she’s dead,” said one of her classmates. “How could anyone do this to her?” 

Police chief Martin Beck warns, “Parents need to know that when their children visit online message boards and social networking sites, there are Internet predators out there who may want to hurt them.”]]>
